FYI, rather than removing `children` from the table altogether (which can imply that it's an unsupported prop), you can remove just the control like so:

```js
children: {
  control: false,
},
```

Alternatively, where appropriate (e.g. Button), you can constrain the `children` control to just a string:

```js
children: {
  control: 'text',
},
```

Docs: https://storybook.js.org/docs/api/arg-types#control (we could do a better job making this more findable üòÖ)
